/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/30\/expiate-sins-increase-rewards\/","url_meta":{"origin":14009,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Deeds to expiate sins, increase rewards","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 30, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cShall I not tell you of that by which Allah expiates your sins and increases your good deeds?\u201d They said, \u201cOf course, O Messenger of Allah.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cThorough ablution despite difficulty, taking many steps to\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":14279,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/05\/19\/parable-five-salawat\/","url_meta":{"origin":14009,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Salah: Example of five prayers is a purifying river","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 19, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir ibn Abdullah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe parable\u00a0of the five prayers is that of a river running at your door\u00a0in which one cleanses himself five times a day.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 668 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u062c\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650\u0631\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32976,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/30\/forgives-between-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":14009,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Allah forgives what one did between prayers","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 30, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Uthman ibn Affan reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cA Muslim man does not perform ablution in an excellent manner and then performs prayer, but that Allah will forgive him for what occurred between his prayer and the next.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 158, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33003,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/30\/perfect-wudu-five-salawat\/","url_meta":{"origin":14009,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Perfect ablution, five prayers expiation of sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 30, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Uthman ibn Affan reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever perfects his ablution as Allah Almighty has commanded him, the prescribed prayers will be an expiation for what occurs between them.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 231 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064f\u062b\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":14284,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadith